Cerclage of cervix during pregnancy by abdominal approach (procedure)

ns0:DescribedValueSet.ns0:Purpose: (Clinical Focus: This value set contains concepts that represent cervical cerclage procedures performed by the abdominal approach.),(Data Element Scope: This value set may use the Quality Data Model (QDM) category related to Procedure. The intent of this value set is to identify patients who have had a transabdominal cerclage.),(Inclusion Criteria: Includes only relevant concepts associated with codes identifying transabdominal cerclage. This is a grouping of ICD-10-PCS codes and SNOMED CT codes.),(Exclusion Criteria: Excludes concepts that pertain to Cervical cerclage procedures performed by any other approach, such as the vaginal approach, should not be included.)
